<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Basic_operations">Basic ope=
rations</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-br=
acket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DBool=
ean_algebra&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D4" title=3D"Edit section: Basic=
 operations"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]<=
/span></span></div><p>
While elementary algebra has four operations (addition, subtraction, multip=
lication, and division), the Boolean algebra has only three basic operation=
s: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Logical_conjunction" title=3D"L=
ogical conjunction">conjunction</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Disjunction" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Disjunction">disjunction</a>=
, and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Negation" title=3D"Negation"=
>negation</a>, expressed with the corresponding <a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/Binary_operator" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Binary operat=
or">binary operators</a> <i>AND</i> (<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-ma=
th-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a1=
1y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/Mat=
hML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle \land }">
  <semantics>
