-align: -2.338ex; width:36.275ex; height:5.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle {\=
begin{aligned}&amp;{\text{Complementation 1}}&amp;x\wedge \neg x&amp;=3D0\\=
&amp;{\text{Complementation 2}}&amp;x\vee \neg x&amp;=3D1\end{aligned}}}"><=
/span></dd></dl>
<p>All properties of negation including the laws below follow from the abov=
e two laws alone.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Givant-Halmos_2009_5-2" class=3D"refer=
ence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boolean_algebra#cite_note-Gi=
vant-Halmos_2009-5"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>5<span class=3D"ci=
te-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>In both ordinary and Boolean algebra, negation works by exchanging p=
airs of elements, hence in both algebras it satisfies the double negation l=
aw (also called involution law)
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e {\begin{aligned}&amp;{\text{Double negation}}&amp;\neg {(\neg {x})}&amp;=
=3Dx\end{aligned}}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mtable columnalign=3D"right left right left right left right lef=
t right left right left" rowspacing=3D"3pt" columnspacing=3D"0em 2em 0em 2e=
m 0em 2em 0em 2em 0em 2em 0em" displaystyle=3D"true">
            <mtr>
              <mtd></mtd>
              <mtd>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mtext>Double negation</mtext>
                </mrow>
              </mtd>
              <mtd>
                <mi mathvariant=3D"normal">=C2=AC<!-- =C2=AC --></mi>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
                  <mi mathvariant=3D"normal">=C2=AC<!-- =C2=AC --></mi>
                  <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                    <mi>x</mi>
                  </mrow>
                  <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
                </mrow>
              </mtd>
              <mtd>
                <mi></mi>
                <mo>=3D</mo>
                <mi>x</mi>
              </mtd>
            </mtr>
          </mtable>
        </mrow>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle {\begin{align=
